Ah yes I see what's happening here. So the new version is checking to see if only one dictionary level is returned, as in: 
```python
{
  "name": "henry"
}
```
rather than 
```python
{
  "-K2QRiOt8oQ5vBYS5mI1":  {
    "name": "henry"
  }, 
  "-K2QfF5GZ2psbso7lEMj": {
    "name": "bob"
  }
}
```
so we don't have to unpack it from a list. Then the first version is checking if we are only returning one primitive e.g. ```"bob"```, so really they should be combined into something like:
```python
# check if dict
if isinstance(request_object.json(), dict):
    # if one level dict return to avoid unpacking list
    if not isinstance(list(request_dict.values())[0], dict):
        return request_dict
else:
    # return primitive
    return request_object.json()
```
Actually that's not quite right, because the request_dict.values() section only checks if the first value is a dict while it is certainly possible the second, third or fourth value could be a dict (as seen in #12). Hmmm will have to think about this a bit.

