Trying to rewrite the directive based on stSearch code, I ended up with this:

```javascript
angula.module('myApp').directive('stSearchModel', [stSearchModel]);

function stSearchModel () {
  return {
    require: '^stTable',
    link: function (scope, element, attr, tableCtrl) {

      scope.$watch(attr.stSearchModel, function (newValue, oldValue) {
        if (newValue !== oldValue) {
          tableCtrl.search(newValue, attr.stPredicate);
        }
      });

      attr.$observe('stPredicate', function (newValue, oldValue) {
        var model = scope.$eval(attr.stSearchModel);
        if (newValue !== oldValue && model) {
          tableCtrl.search(model, newValue);
        }
      });
    }
  };
}
```

And got the very same error when triggering updates on `st-search` input.

Trying to debug it, I found that passing any predicate to `st-search` made it work smoothly with both the `stSearchModel` and `stFilterColumn` directives. So this works:

```html
<div class="col-md-3">
  <input st-search="$" class="form-control" placeholder="FILTER" type="text"/>
  <div st-filter-column="sortData1" filter-value="{{filterValue}}"></div>
</div>
```

But this doesn't:

```html
<div class="col-md-3">
  <input st-search class="form-control" placeholder="FILTER" type="text"/>
  <div st-filter-column="sortData1" filter-value="{{filterValue}}"></div>
</div>
```

Explicitly setting the predicate to "$" is not big deal, but not setting it at all should not be a problem. Any suggestions on how to workaround it from these directives?

Thanks.

