I don't have the time today to grok what the underlying issue actually is, but I've had good luck in the past with writing my own tiny tiny .so's to exercise weird linker issues -- like you can generate a set of .so's with a funky transitive dependency with just this much writing:
```
-- a.c --
extern int from_b();
extern int from_c();
int from_a() {
    return from_b() + from_c();
}

-- b.c --
extern int from_c();
int from_b() {
    return 2 * from_c();
}

-- c.c --
int from_c() {
    return 1;
}

-- build.sh --
gcc c.c -o c.so -shared
gcc b.c -o b.so -shared -L. -lc
# a.so links directly to b.so but not to c.so
gcc a.c -o a.so -shared -L. -lb
```

